I stayed in touch with Dr Ikiara, who continued to write for the papers where I worked. In 2004, he summoned me to his office at the Ministry of Transport, where he was the Permanent Secretary. He was livid. I was managing editor of the Standard and a columnist for the Sunday Standard. He is an avuncular guy, very thoughtful, kind and polite but on this occasion he was firing from barrels I did not know he had.



